node_modules/
dist/
.DS_Store
*.log

# The village's disposable stores and seeds (the code and docs are tracked; see demos/village/README.md)
demos/village/homes/
site-dist/

# `.claude/` is local session state EXCEPT the prosecution lenses, which are a reviewed, versioned
# defense and belong to the repo. Written as a wildcard + negation rather than `.claude/`, because
# git will not descend into an excluded DIRECTORY — a negation under `.claude/` would never match.
# Same ordering rule as the .adlc block below: the wildcard must stay above every negation.
.claude/*
!.claude/agents/
!.claude/agents/**

# ADLC runtime — an ALLOWLIST, and `adlc init` owns these lines. What is committed is the CONTRACT
# (config, tickets, specs); everything else under .adlc/ — findings.jsonl, manifest.jsonl,
# ticket-transactions/ — is per-worktree evidence that gates assert against locally, and committing
# it would collide across branches. If an adlc upgrade adds a new contract file, re-run `adlc init`
# to pick up its negation rather than hand-adding one here.
#
# ORDER IS LOAD-BEARING: `.adlc/*` must stay FIRST. git is last-match-wins, so a negation above it
# is dead. `adlc ticket store migrate --write` has been seen to reorder this block and strand
# `!.adlc/config.json` above the wildcard — check `git check-ignore -v --no-index .adlc/config.json`
# after any adlc command that touches this file.
.adlc/*
!.adlc/config.json
!.adlc/tickets.json
!.adlc/tickets/
!.adlc/tickets/**
!.adlc/ticket-archive/
!.adlc/ticket-archive/**
!.adlc/specs/

# A failed rename leaves an orphaned temp file wearing this shape (archive.ts writes
# <target>.<pid>.tmp then renames); a mutation run does it in the repo root. Never committable —
# one of these once carried the erasure canary INTO git history on the PR about byte-erasure.
/*.tmp
